	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />For example, if you have 32KB of data to fill a 256KB EPROM you can just write the same data 8 times. You can generate the file with the repeated data like this in the command prompt or in a batch file: <strong>copy /b prg32.prg + prg32.prg + prg32.prg + prg32.prg + prg32.prg + prg32.prg + prg32.prg + prg32.prg prg256.prg</strong>

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


